# Python API

Keep HTTP transport code thin and push behavior into testable services.

## Rules

- Keep route handlers small and explicit.
- Validate inputs at the API boundary.
- Keep network calls timeout-bound and error-aware.
- Prefer deterministic app-factory tests for starter behavior.
- Use an ASGI test client only when request/response integration behavior matters.
- Do not start live servers in unit tests.
- Keep health checks deterministic and dependency-light.

## Commands

```bash
make test
uv run pytest tests/unit/test_smoke.py
uv run {{ project_slug }}
```
